reviewText: Good work out, not too strenuous, but you can work as hard or as easy as you want.

I love this work out I bought this workout to add to my diverse DVD collection of workout video's. This work out is simple and slow. It is a great starter video for anyone who has not worked out in awhile. It is not intense just a get you to move video. If you are looking for a hard workout this is not for you. If you are getting started this is for you.

I had bought this video few years ago and enjoyed it so much. However, a friend borrowed it and I never saw it again. Perfect for a whole body conditioning  in a  short amount  of time. Sugar and Laila are great instructors.
This is a really good workout.  I like that they explain the steps.  I also like the different levels of it.
if you don't like jumping due to bad knees this one maybe for you. I enjoyed watching boxing throughout my life and now i can exercise with two of the great champs.
I'm glad I got this vid from the library because it would be horrible if I had spent money on it.  The cueing is horrible, and downright frustrating.  I turned this off and put P90x Cardio X back on.

Very poor instruction and poor cuing.  They may know boxing but they aren't good at leading a class.  Even the count pacing gets thrown off here and there.  If you must try check it out from the library.
